{"session_id": 47, "bill_id": 13445, "bill_type": "House Bill", "bill_number": 1046, "bill_title": "to provide for rule-making authority for the sale of health and life insurance.", "sponsors": [], "keywords": ["Administrative Rules", "Health Insurance", "Insurance (See also Health Ins, Motor Vehicle Ins)"], "audio": [], "bill_versions": [{"bill_id": 13445, "bill_version_id": 77256, "bill_version": "Introduced", "bill_version_date": "1998-01-10T00:00:00-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to provide for rule-making authority for the sale of health and life insurance. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 58-33 be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: The director may promulgate rules, pursuant to chapter 1-26, pertaining to the advertising, sale, and solicitation of life and health insurance. In promulgating these rules, the director shall consider existing National Association of Insurance Commissioner's model laws and regulations including the Advertising of Accident and Sickness Insurance, Individual Accident and Sickness Insurance Minimum Standards Act, Model Regulation to Implement the Individual Accident Sickness Insurance Minimum Standards Act, Uniform Individual Accident and Sickness Policy Provisions Law, Advertising of Life Insurance, Buyer's Guide for Life Insurance, Life Insurance Disclosure Model Regulation, the impact the rules would have upon the life and health insurance markets in this state and the need for the protection of the insurance buying public in this state. The rules may include: (1) Definition of terms; (2) Content and style of advertisements and solicitation materials; (3) Prohibited practices and minimum standards; (4) Disclosure requirements including the use of prescribed forms, guides, indices, and summaries; (5) Record retention and reporting requirements; (6) Dividend and death benefit calculations; and (7) Compliance procedures."}], "amendments":